			<Folder>
				<name>Water Seeker</name>
				<description>Dry-season afternoon movement toward Walayar Lake. Elephants visit permanent water once daily (14:00–18:00) during dry season. Strong directional bias toward large water bodies. Refs: Varma et al. 2012 (Walayar); Wall et al. 2006; Chamaille-Jammes et al. 2007 (density ∝ exp(−d/λ), λ≈2.2 km).</description>
				<Placemark>
					<name>Water Seeker path</name>
					<styleUrl>#sty_Water_Seeker</styleUrl>
